The paper deals with improving user identification performance in massive machine type communications using a deep learning aided list approximate message passing (AMP) algorithm. This involves the use of a neural network to identify a suspicious device and enforce it to be inactive in every iteration of the AMP algorithm. The paper thus involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE), and control systems (cs.SY).
